Dav

Target IP: 10.10.236.127

Scanning


There is only open one TCP port open on the target machine: HTTP on 80.

Enumeration


The default Apache webpage is displayed for this port. However, doing a directory search shows there is a directory called /webdav which asks for the username and password.


Running a curl request against this directory shows the authentication method used is webdav.

Exploitation


I tried the default credential wampp:xampp and I gained access to the /webdav page.



I used the command curl --user 'wampp:xampp' 'http://10.10.236.127/webdav/' -T shell.php to upload a PHP Pentest Monkey reverse shell script on the target machine. The HTTP response code is 201, meaning the file was uploaded successfully.


I started a listener on port 8443 and visited the /shell.php and gained a reverse shell connection. And now I have a foothold on the target machine.

Privilege Escalation


Looks like /bin/cat binary can be used with sudo for PE. I obtained the shadow file which contains the password hash of merlin, but I was unable to crack the password using john. I was unable to obtain the SSH key, bash_history, and any other useful files of the user root.

Flags


The user.txt flag once I gained a foothold on the machine.


The root.txt flag once I used cat to obtain this flag.
